#Step 1: Store Wallpaper & Lock Screen Files Centrally
#Since SYSVOL doesn’t replicate between domains, you have two options:
#Option A (Best Practice – Per Domain SYSVOL)
#Copy raadesktop.png and RAAcolor.png into each domain’s SYSVOL. Example:
    \\randa.local\SYSVOL\randa.local\scripts\wallpapers\
    \\haggarclothing.com\SYSVOL\haggarclothing.com\scripts\wallpapers\
    \\tribal-inc.com\SYSVOL\tribal-inc.com\scripts\wallpapers\
    \\totescorp.com\SYSVOL\totescorp.com\scripts\wallpapers\
    \\haggarcanada.com\SYSVOL\haggarcanada.com\scripts\wallpapers\
    \randa.randacorp.com\SYSVOL\randa.randacorp.com\scripts\wallpapers\
#Option B (Central File Server – Cross-Domain Access)
#Place images on a central share, e.g.:
    \\odc2fs01\randa-gpo\wallpapers\
#Grant Read permissions to Domain Computers and Domain Users from all six domains.
#Use this UNC path in every GPO.

#Step 2: Create the GPO in Each Domain
#For each domain, open GPMC (from a DC in that domain or via trust) → right-click the domain root → Create a GPO in this domain, and Link it here…
#Name it consistently across all domains:
    RAA - Desktop, Lock Screen, Security, Logon Message

#Step 3: Configure GPO Settings
#Repeat the configuration in each domain GPO:
#Desktop Wallpaper:
    User Config → Policies → Admin Templates → Desktop → Desktop Wallpaper
    Path: \\<server>\randa-gpo\wallpapers\raadesktop.png
#Lock Screen:
    Computer Config → Policies → Admin Templates → Control Panel → Personalization → Force a specific default lock screen and logon image
    Path: \\<server>\randa-gpo\wallpapers\RAAcolor.png
#Prevent Screen Saver Change:
    User Config → Policies → Admin Templates → Control Panel → Personalization → Prevent changing screen saver → Enabled
#Idle Timeout (10 min)
    Computer Config → Policies → Windows Settings → Security Settings → Local Policies → Security Options
    Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit → 600 seconds
#Logon Banner:
    Title: Randa Apparel & Accessories PC Usage Policy
    Text: (full usage policy text you provided)

#Step 4: Apply & Test Per Domain
#After creating each GPO, force an update:
    gpupdate /force
#Test in each domain by logging into a workstation.

#Step 5: Confirm
#Once tested, you can confirm back to leadership:
“The RAA - Desktop, Lock Screen, Security, Logon Message GPO has been created and linked across all six domains (randa.local, haggarclothing.com, tribal-inc.com, totescorp.com, haggarcanada.com, randa.randacorp.com). The wallpaper, lock screen, inactivity limit, and logon message are enforced. Please advise if additional adjustments are needed.”